AWS is a library containing functions to perform the
Propagation-Separation approach as introduced in

[1] Polzehl, J. and Spokoiny, V. (2004). Propagation-Separation Approach for Local Likelihood Estimation}, Manuskript, 2004.

and

[2] Polzehl, J. and Spokoiny, V. (2004). Spatially adaptive regression estimation: Propagation-separation approach, WIAS-Preprint No. 998, 2004.

and the stagewise aggregation approach, see

[2] Belomestny and Spokoiny, V. (2004). Local likelihood modeling via stagewise aggregation,
WIAS-Preprint No. 1000



URL: http://www.wias-berlin.de/project-areas/stat/projects/awspapers.html


Joerg Polzehl
email: polzehl@wias-berlin.de
